    <modellingAndValidation>
      <representativeness systemModelId="290c1f85-4cc4-4fa1-b0c8-2cb7f4276dce">
        <systemModelName xml:lang="en">Allocation, cut-off by classification</systemModelName>
        <samplingProcedure xml:lang="en">Data obtained from the literature. 
References:
Ioannou, I., Javaloyes-Antón, J., Caballero, J. A., &amp; Guillén-Gosálbez, G. (2023). Economic and Environmental Performance of an Integrated CO2 Refinery. ACS Sustainable Chemistry &amp; Engineering, 11(5), 1949-1961.

Due to the fact that that there are two  reference products in this dataset, subdivision of the exchange amounts between ethylene and propylene is required first. This subdivision is based on the shares of mass from the respective products. The ethylene contribution is 1 kg while propylene contribute roughly 0.66 kg. The resulting fractions for the subdivision are approximately 60.24 and 39.76% for ethylene, propylene, and butenes, respectively. Meaning that 60.24% of the exchanges are allocated to ethylene production and the remaining 37.76% are allocated to propylene production.
</samplingProcedure>
        <extrapolations xml:lang="en">Literature data.</extrapolations>
      </representativeness>
